eferrer\">According to<\/a> Blockworks, Raydium&rsquo;s meme coin factory, called LaunchLab, will maintain a similar bonding curve as Pump.fun but will differentiate by allowing third-party user interfaces to set fees.<\/p><p>Plus, the platform will support multiple quote tokens and link with Raydium&rsquo;s liquidity provider locker for perpetual swap fee security.<\/p><p>The development of LaunchLab surfaced less than a month after Pump.fun reportedly tested its own AMM, a move that signaled its intention to pull away from Raydium.<\/p><p>This could hugely impact Raydium, which has derived substantial revenue from Pump.fun&rsquo;s token pools.<\/p><p>Rumors of Pump.fun&rsquo;s AMM feature triggered a 30% drop in RAY&rsquo;s value, CoinMarketCap <a href=\"https:\/\/coinmarketcap.com\/currencies\/raydium\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">data<\/a> shows.<\/p><p>This decline intensified as the crypto market experienced a widespread correction shortly thereafter, fueled by escalating tariff tensions and a deteriorating macroeconomic environment.<\/p><p>In the past month, RAY has plummeted by around 60%.<\/p><h2>Declining interest in meme coins<\/h2><p>Pump.fun&rsquo;s graduation rate, which refers to the percentage of tokens that successfully transition from the incubation phase to full tradability on a Solana DEX, has been below 1% since February 17, <a href=\"https:\/\/dune.com\/adam_tehc\/pumpfun\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">according to<\/a> Dune Analytics.<\/p><figure><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/static.cryptobriefing.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/03\/18232301\/Pump.funs-graduation-rate-down-below-1.png\"><figcaption><\/figcaption><\/figure><p>Historically, the highest graduation rate was 1.67% in November 2024, but even then, the absolute number of successful tokens was significant due to the large volume of launches.<\/p><p>The current low graduation rate reflects declining investor interest in meme coins, commonly perceived as high-risk investments.<\/p><p>According to CoinMarketCap <a href=\"https:\/\/coinmarketcap.com\/view\/memes\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">data<\/a>, the meme coin sector&rsquo;s market cap is down around 65% from its peak on December 9 last year.<\/p><html><body><div class=\"ad-banner mrec-in-article\"><div class=\"code-block code-block-4 ai-track\" data-ai=\"WzQsIiIsIk1SRUMgSW4tYXJ0aWNsZSAtIDMwMHgyNTAiLCIiLDFd\" style=\"margin: 8px 0; clear: both; width: 300px; height: 250px;\">\n\n<div class=\"ai-rotate ai-unprocessed ai-rotate-4-69677372\" data-shares=\"WzEwMF0=\" style=\"position: relative;\">\n<div class=\"ai-rotate-option\" style=\"visibility: hidden;\" data-index=\"1\" data-name=\"U2V2aW8=\">\n<div style=\"width: 300px; height: 250px\">\n<script async src=\"https:\/\/cdn.adx.ws\/scripts\/loader.js\"><\/script>\n<div class=\"sevioads\" data-zone=\"e895191b-6d01-4021-992d-173ebfdf2d63\"><\/div>\n<script>\n    window.sevioads = window.sevioads || [];\n    var sevioads_preferences = [];\n    sevioads_preferences[0] = {};\n    sevioads_preferences[0].zone = \"e895191b-6d01-4021-992d-173ebfdf2d63\";\n    sevioads_preferences[0].adType = \"banner\";\n    sevioads_preferences[0].inventoryId = \"c5700508-581b-472c-8fdd-a931cdbfc8e1\";\n    sevioads_preferences[0].accountId = \"1e47efc1-ec2d-4fca-a8b9-354e249e5095\";\n    sevioads.push(sevioads_preferences);\n<\/script>\n<\/div><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<script>if (typeof ai_js_code == 'boolean') {var ai_block_div = document.querySelector ('.ai-rotate-4-69677372'); ai_process_rotation (ai_block_div); ai_block_div.classList.remove ('ai-rotate-4-69677372');};<\/script>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/body><\/html><p>Despite short-lived optimism ahead of Trump&rsquo;s inauguration, the majority of meme tokens were in a bloodbath post-inauguration date.<\/p><figure><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/static.cryptobriefing.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/03\/18232053\/meme-tokens-were-in-a-bloodbath-post-inauguration-date.png\"><figcaption><\/figcaption><\/figure><p>And despite slight improvements in liquidity, the overall crypto market, including Bitcoin, remains under pressure with no major recovery in sight for meme coins.<\/p><p>That being said, while Raydium&rsquo;s established presence could provide a competitive edge, the debut of its meme coin launchpad may face initial hurdles.<\/p><p>Commenting on Raydium&rsquo;s move, Ceteris, Head of Research at Delphi Digital, said that Raydium will likely encounter a fundamental issue of user engagement.<\/p><p>While Raydium provides the underlying liquidity infrastructure, platforms like Pump.fun and aggregators such as Jupiter effectively control the user interface and experience, according to the analyst.<\/p><blockquote><p>&ldquo;Pump.fun owns the user, Raydium is just back-end infra. Even when users go to trade after bonding they go to Jupiter. [Most probably] don&rsquo;t even realize they&rsquo;re Raydium pools,&rdquo; Ceteris <a href=\"https:\/\/x.com\/ceterispar1bus\/status\/1902136704569430263\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">said<\/a>. &ldquo;Much harder to own the user than to create a vanilla AMM.&rdquo;<\/p><\/blockquote><p>Story Protocol&rsquo;s Jongwon Park added, &ldquo;in fact, crypto UX gets better when you abstract away 10s of AMMs. Products are king, and liquidity in AMM follows products.&rdquo;<\/p>\n\n        \n        \n                    <section class=\"article-share\">\n  <p>Share this article<\/p>\n  <div class=\"social-icons\">\n          <button class=\"social-icon share\" data-href=\"https:\/\/x.com\/intent\/tweet?text=RAY+jumps+28%25+after+Raydium+unveils+Pump.fun%E2%80%99s+meme+coin+launchpad+rival&url=https%3A%2F%2Fcryptobriefing.com%2Fraydium-competes-with-pump-fun%2F&via=crypto_briefing\" aria-label=\"Share on x\">\n        <?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n                <svg xm